**Code Explanation:**

This script performs the molecular cooling threshold analysis and cosmic metallicity evolution comparison for Step 5. It loads the z_form CSV from Step 1/2, applies stellar-to-halo mass conversion using epsilon = 0.01–0.05 (appropriate for high-redshift low-mass halos where star formation efficiency is suppressed by feedback and shallow potential wells), compares implied halo masses to molecular and atomic cooling thresholds, implements the Maiolino et al. (2008) MZR parameterization (which gives 12+log(O/H) as a function of log10(M_star) and redshift), converts to [Z/H] using solar oxygen abundance 12+log(O/H)_solar = 8.69, evaluates the MZR at median stellar masses and formation redshifts for both systems, and computes the observed vs. predicted metallicity offsets. All units: masses in solar masses (M_sun), metallicities in [Z/H] = log10(Z/Z_sun), redshifts dimensionless, ages in Gyr.

